SVM Classification¶

Images taken from https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/support-vector-machine-algorithm/

SVM hyperparameters¶

The C parameter

The C parameter is inversely proportional to the margin size, this means that the larger the value of C, the smaller the margin, and, conversely, the smaller the value of C, the larger the margin. The C parameter can be used along with any kernel, it tells the algorithm how much to avoid misclassifying each training sample, due to that, it is also known as regularization.

The gamma hyperparameter The gamma hyperparameter ,like C, is somewhat inversely proportional to its distance. The higher its value, the closest are the points that are considered for the decision boundary, and the lowest the gamma, the farther points are also considered for choosing the decision boundary.

Source:https://stackabuse.com/understanding-svm-hyperparameters/
